Subject: [eVuln] microBlog BBCode XSS Vulnerability


New eVuln Advisory:
microBlog BBCode XSS Vulnerability
http://evuln.com/vulns/36/summary/bt/

--------------------Summary----------------

Software: microBlog
Sowtware's Web Site: http://www.stamcar.com/projekti/microblog/
Versions: 2.0 RC-10
Critical Level: Harmless
Type: Cross-Site Scripting
Class: Remote
Status: Unpatched
Exploit: Available
Solution: Not Available
Discovered by: Aliaksandr Hartsuyeu (eVuln.com)
eVuln ID: EV0036

-----------------Description---------------
Arbitrary script code insertion is possible in BBcode [url] tag.

Vulnerable Script: functions.php

[url] tag isn't properly sanitized. This can be used to post arbitrary script code.

--------------Exploit----------------------
Available at: http://evuln.com/vulns/36/exploit/bt/


--------------Solution---------------------
No Patch available.

